PRPLX-20: Contractor and Part-Time Staff Governance Onboarding Addresses: Shadow AI Use / Insufficient Governance Onboarding Contractor onboarding module published in LMS. Enforced as hard prerequisite in access provisioning workflow. No contractor or part-time staff access granted without completion. Primary control for Insufficient Governance Onboarding risk.

Citation Verification and Output Validation Requirements 
All Perplexity outputs used to inform a material business decision require citation verification before the output is acted upon. Hallucination is an inherent characteristic of all large language models powering this platform. Citation presence does not guarantee accuracy. Every employee, contractor, and part-time staff member is individually accountable for the accuracy of work product that incorporates Perplexity outputs. Hallucination does not transfer accountability away from the user.
All AI-generated content intended for external distribution requires citation verification and organizational approval before distribution to prevent Hallucinated Output Distribution. AI-generated content is never a final external deliverable without this validation step confirmed.
All Computer agentic feature actions require user confirmation of action scope before execution in any connected production system. Uncontrolled Agentic Execution is a High probability risk. No agentic action may bypass user confirmation under any circumstance. Any unexpected agentic behavior constitutes an Uncontrolled Agentic Execution event and must be reported to IT immediately.

Monitoring Requirements 
The following monitoring activities are required on an ongoing basis following platform go-live:
Audit Log Monitoring Full audit logging enabled in the Security Hub from day one. The IT Security Administrator conducts formal quarterly reviews covering all queries, file uploads, connector access events, agentic actions, and administrative changes. Any activity indicating Data Leakage / PII Exposure, Least Privilege Violation, Prompt Injection, or Uncontrolled Agentic Execution is escalated to Legal and executive leadership within 48 hours.
Adoption and Training Tracking The AI Governance Lead monitors platform adoption rates and training completion across all departments and user types continuously. Departments falling below the minimum training completion threshold have access suspended pending remediation. Shadow AI Use risk increases directly in proportion to low adoption and Insufficient Governance Onboarding. Quarterly adoption reports delivered to leadership.
Connector Permission Reviews All connected file repository permissions reviewed quarterly to confirm least privilege access is maintained. Any permission scope creep identified constitutes a Least Privilege Violation event and triggers immediate remediation.
Zero Data Retention and Vendor Monitoring The AI Governance Lead maintains an active subscription to Perplexity's release notes, security advisories, and policy updates. Any material change to data retention policies or third-party model provider agreements triggers a governance review within 30 days. A disclosed security incident at the vendor level triggers an immediate Zero Data Retention Breach exposure assessment.
Incident Pattern Analysis The AI Governance Lead reviews all AI-related incident reports monthly. Incidents are categorized by named risk: Hallucination, Data Leakage / PII Exposure, Least Privilege Violation, Prompt Injection, Uncontrolled Agentic Execution, Shadow AI Use, Unauthorized Data Retention, or Hallucinated Output Distribution / Unauthorized Data Leakage. Patterns indicating systemic risk trigger an immediate control review and escalation to leadership.

Semi-Annual Governance Review The AI Governance Lead conducts a full semi-annual review of this Model Card, the Risk Assessment, and the Control Library. All documents updated within 30 days of the review. Business Owner annual reaffirmation required at contract renewal.

Approval Recommendation Conditionally Approved
Based on the completed Platform Assessment, Risk Assessment (02-Risk-Assessments), and AI Control Library (03-Control-Library), the Office of AI Governance recommends Conditional Approval for enterprise-wide deployment of Perplexity Enterprise Pro across all full-time employees, contractors, and part-time staff, subject to the following conditions being met prior to go-live:
All 20 PRPLX controls must be implemented and evidence confirmed by the IT Security Administrator and AI Governance Lead before any user access is provisioned.
The Acceptable Use Policy must be published and acknowledgment collected from all users before access is granted. No exceptions for contractors or part-time staff. Shadow AI Use / Insufficient Governance Onboarding is rated High probability and is directly mitigated by this requirement.
The Business Associate Agreement status with Perplexity AI must be confirmed by Legal before go-live. HIPAA Non-Compliance risk remains unmitigated until the BAA is executed. PHI-adjacent use cases remain prohibited until that condition is met.
The Zero Data Retention policy must be confirmed in writing in the executed vendor contract before go-live. A Zero Data Retention Breach cannot be remediated after the fact. This confirmation is a non-negotiable prerequisite.
The contractor and part-time staff governance onboarding module must be live in the LMS and enforced as a hard prerequisite in the access provisioning workflow before any non-FTE user is granted access. Shadow AI Use / Insufficient Governance Onboarding is rated High probability and is directly driven by this population.
Citation verification requirements for Hallucination mitigation, organizational approval requirements for Hallucinated Output Distribution prevention, and user confirmation requirements for Uncontrolled Agentic Execution prevention must be documented in the AUP, communicated to all department heads, and confirmed as understood before go-live.
Once all conditions are met and evidence is documented, platform status moves from Conditionally Approved to Approved for enterprise use. This Model Card must be reviewed and reaffirmed semi-annually by the AI Governance Lead and annually by the Business Owner.

